        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(agents): honor disabled envelope timestamps at model boundary",
        "body": "Opened on behalf of Onur Solmaz (`osolmaz`). AI-assisted contribution.\n\n## Summary\n\nOpenClaw could still send timestamp bytes to model input even when `agents.defaults.envelopeTimestamp` was `\"off\"`.\nThat matters for cache-sensitive local inference servers such as DS4, where users may want completely bare user-turn bytes.\nThis change routes the existing config through the direct timestamp helper and embedded LLM-boundary normalization while keeping timestamp injection enabled by default.\nIt also adds provider-payload tests showing that timestamps do not bust the reusable prompt prefix when timestamping stays enabled.\n\n## What Changed\n\nThe existing config already disabled channel envelope timestamps, but two model-input paths did not read that setting.\nThis change makes those paths use the same timestamp inclusion decision.\n\n- Added an `includeTimestamp` option to the gateway timestamp helper.\n- Made `timestampOptsFromConfig()` set `includeTimestamp: false` when `agents.defaults.envelopeTimestamp` is `\"off\"`.\n- Added the same toggle to embedded LLM-boundary normalization so current and historical user messages can stay bare for cache-sensitive runs.\n- Passed the toggle through prompt precheck and hook normalization paths that render LLM-boundary message bytes.\n- Added regression coverage for both the direct helper and LLM-boundary behavior.\n- Added timestamp-on provider payload coverage for OpenAI Chat Completions and OpenAI Responses to verify that the stable prefix is byte-identical when a user turn moves from current to history.\n\n## Compatibility And Migration\n\nThere is no persistent schema change and no migration is required.\nThe changed code only affects runtime prompt text construction and tests; it does not change stored transcript shape, database schema, cache storage files, package metadata, or migration code.\n\nThe compatibility change is intentional: `agents.defaults.envelopeTimestamp: \"off\"` now means timestamp text is off for the relevant model-input timestamp paths too, not only formatted channel envelopes.\nThe default behavior is unchanged because timestamping remains on unless this existing config key is explicitly set to `\"off\"`.\nUsers who set `envelopeTimestamp: \"off\"` and still depended on model-visible timestamp prefixes should remove that setting to keep timestamps.\n\n## Cache Behavior\n\nTurning timestamps off is not required for prompt-cache stability in the normal embedded path.\nWith timestamping enabled, OpenClaw stamps each user message from that message's stored timestamp, so the same old message serializes the same way when it is current and when it is replayed as history.\nThe provider-payload tests also assert that the next turn's timestamp appears after the stable prefix, not before it.\n\n## Testing\n\nI reproduced the disabled-timestamp issue first with a failing boundary test.\nBefore the fix, the new test received `[Wed 2024-06-05 07:01 UTC] Cache-sensitive current ask` when it expected bare text.\nAfter the fix, the focused gateway, boundary, provider-payload, lint, format, and type checks pass.\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/gateway/server-methods/server-methods.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/attempt.llm-boundary.test.ts --reporter=verbose`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/attempt.llm-boundary.cache-stability.test.ts --reporter=verbose`\n- `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs src/gateway/server-methods/agent-timestamp.ts src/gateway/server-methods/server-methods.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/attempt.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/attempt.llm-boundary.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/attempt.llm-boundary.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/attempt.llm-boundary.cache-stability.test.ts`\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/attempt.llm-boundary.cache-stability.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `pnpm tsgo:core`\n- `pnpm tsgo:test:src`\n\nI did not run a live DS4 cache-read measurement.\nThe added proof is source-level and provider-payload-level: it verifies the bytes OpenClaw builds before sending the model request.\n\n## Risks\n\nThe default behavior is unchanged because timestamp injection still stays on unless config explicitly sets `envelopeTimestamp: \"off\"`.\nThe main risk is compatibility for users who disabled envelope timestamps but still relied on gateway-injected or LLM-boundary model timestamps; this change makes the config name behave more literally across model-input paths.\n\n## Related Context\n\nRelated external discussion: https://github.com/antirez/ds4/pull/412\n",
        "branch": "fix/ds4-envelope-off-repro",
